Yen Weakens as Japan’s Noda Says G-7 Will Coordinate Currency Intervention

-- B y   Y o s h i a k i   N o h a r a
-- 
2011-03-18T00:05:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/yen-weakens-as-japan-s-noda-says-g-7-will-coordinate-currency-intervention.html
The yen weakened after Japanese
Finance Minister  Yoshihiko Noda  said today that some Group of
Seven nations will perform joint currency intervention.    Japan ’s currency fell to 80.47 to the dollar as of 9:04
a.m. in  Tokyo  from 78.89 in  New York  yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
